+{"id":"bd-xapiq","title":"PORT: 8 libcrypt aliases + DES no-op stubs + crypt_preferred_method + crypt_checksalt","description":"Add 8 libcrypt aliases / fail-safe stubs to close part of the libcrypt parity gap. Our existing crypt() already supports MD5/SHA-256/SHA-512; these add the historical names + DES no-ops + utility queries that programs commonly link against without actually invoking crypto. (1) fcrypt(key, salt) — alias of crypt. (2) xcrypt(key, salt) — same. (3) encrypt(block, edflag) — no-op (DES single-block; DES is obsolete and our crypt rejects it anyway). (4) encrypt_r(block, edflag, *data) — no-op. (5) setkey(key) — no-op. (6) setkey_r(key, *data) — no-op. (7) crypt_preferred_method() -> *const c_char — return the static string \"$6$\" (SHA-512 = our strongest supported method). (8) crypt_checksalt(setting) -> int — parse the salt prefix; return CRYPT_SALT_OK (= 0) for $1$/$5$/$6$ and CRYPT_SALT_INVALID (= 1) otherwise per libxcrypt convention.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-26T17:53:20.521744556Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T17:53:20.521744556Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
